HEADWORD: Furze
<hw>Furze</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>firs</ets>,
As. <ets>fyrs</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A thorny evergreen
shrub (<spn>Ulex Europ⟦ae⟧us</spn>), with beautiful yellow flowers, very
common upon the plains and hills of Great Britain; -- called also
<altname>gorse</altname>, and <altname>whin</altname>. The dwarf furze
is <spn>Ulex nanus</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

